text: René Teulade (17 June 1931 - 13 February 2014) was a French politician and civil servant. He was a member of the Senate of France, representing the Corrèze department. He was a member of the Socialist Party. He was born in Monceaux-sur-Dordogne, Corrèze. Teulade died from a stroke on 13 February 2014 in Paris.
